Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Djibouti and specific medical facilities set up to treat patients.
Entry restrictions
The Republic of Djibouti suspended all international commercial passenger flights to and from Djibouti from 18 March until at least 1 September. Land borders are also closed until at least 1 September.
If you are in Djibouti and you need to extend your visa you should contact the Djiboutian Department of Immigration.
Local measures
Facemasks are now mandatory when out in public. Some shops and public transport will reopen on 17 May, places of worship on 23 May, and restaurants on 15 June. Keep up to date with information from your tour operator, transport or accommodation
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
